tVmluc29uLVN5bmRyb21lPC9wPg==\" id=\"Lf06c5ac2bca8870990ce3aff610a8267\" data-source=\"Lf06c5ac2bca8870990ce3aff610a8267\">PVS</span> due to nontraumatic etiology → recovery unlikely after <span class=\"nowrap\">≥ 3 months</span>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Low <span data-phrasegroup-id=\"l2Wv3k0\" data-type=\"bonus\" class=\"api dictionary\" data-content=\"\" id=\"Le56ddc3b2a4d1d3e7cc91e3ed1139a63\" data-source=\"Le56ddc3b2a4d1d3e7cc91e3ed1139a63\">life expectancy</span> <span class=\"condensed-hidden\"><span class=\"api explanation\" data-type=\"bonus\" data-content=\"\" id=\"Ed887c6722edb245ecd99ac912ce54647\"></span></span>\n</li>\n<li>\n<span class=\"api\" data-type=\"link\" data-anker=\"Z81ae5ef3f8b5df3782d1b330374d6b05\" data-learningcard-id=\"1E02u3\" data-lxid=\"1E02u3\" data-section-id=\"YSdny60\" data-sxid=\"YSdny60\" data-title=\"R29hbHMgb2YgY2FyZSDihpIgTGltaXRhdGlvbiBvZiBsaWZlLXN1c3RhaW5pbmcgdHJlYXRtZW50\" id=\"L2dadde9eab16d2d4bbfacd9f683c0bcb\" data-source=\"L2dadde9eab16d2d4bbfacd9f683c0bcb\">Withdrawal of life support</span> may be considered if the chances of recovery are very low (e.g., <span class=\"nowrap\">≥ 12 months</span> in traumatic <span data-phrasegroup-id=\"SgVyuF0\" data-type=\"bonus\" class=\"api dictionary\" data-content=\"PHA+QW4gYWJicmV2aWF0aW9uIHRoYXQgY2FuIHJlZmVyIHRvOjxicj4NCjEuIFBlcnNpc3RlbnQgdmVnZXRhdGl2ZSBzdGF0ZTxicj4NCjIuIFBsdW1tZXItVmluc29uLVN5bmRyb21lPC9wPg==\" id=\"La731ef90e45a223e6334a3e8eeea0cae\" data-source=\"La731ef90e45a223e6334a3e8eeea0cae\">PVS</span>). However, in patients without advanced directives, it is a complicated legal and ethical question that requires discussion with family members and experts.</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"condensed-hidden\"><span class=\"unwichtig\">References:<span data-type=\"Reference\" data-eid=\"-PYDh6\" data-page=\"\" data-cmt=\"\" data-ref-index=\"1\">[1]</span><span data-type=\"Reference\" data-eid=\"Z4YZ36\" data-page=\"1327–1338\" data-cmt=\"\" data-ref-index=\"2\">[2]</span></span></p>\n\n<!--no-condensed--><ul class=\"condensed-hidden\"><li>Treatment is supportive; no definitive treatment exists.</li></ul>\n\n            "
